{
  "stem": "3360.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It got to be-- well, when, when my uncle was released from, from the [GERMAN], they called it-- 'KZ.' The concentration camp was called 'Kah Zed' for short-- K, 'kah,' 'zed.' That's the German letters.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] He talked about-- he wasn't much worse for the experience, except-- because they, they were strong.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's brothers were strong people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were not mollycoddled.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were-- my-- her older brother had been in World War I.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This younger brother had not.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But this younger brother had-- during the bad years in Germany, where all these parties were fighting for one another and the communists were trying to take over, he had fought what was called the 'Red Army' in Germany, at a certain point in time in the '20s.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was too young to be in the World War I army.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But he had actually fought in the streets the communists, as a good German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And because of that-- and he had documentation from the authorities, which his wife presented-- because of that, he got out very soon.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He got out of the concentration camp near Hamburg very soon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My mother's other brother in [GERMAN], who was incarcerated in the-- in the concentration camp near Berlin, then first went to his sister there in Berlin, where I had stayed.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he told all the stories about all the horrible things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But he, too, wasn't much worse for the experience.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They talked about the-- the-- those who were in the worst physical condition, how they would go at those first, knock their heads against the wall until the brains spilled out.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
